@NODE #bubble "MUI Bubble help"
	@{B}Bubble Help
	-----------@{UB}

	Image Descriptor make use of MUI Bubble Help.

	Almost each element of GUI has its own bubble help. Just wait few seconds
	and bubble should appear with short explanation of gadget you point on.

	If bubble doesnt appear after few seconds please check your settings in
	@{"MUI Prefs" system MUI:MUI} program.
@ENDNODE
@NODE #9 "ARexx Support"
	@{B}ARexx Support
	-------------@{UB}

	Since version 2.3, Image Descriptor provides an ARexx
	interface.

	Please read @{"id2arexx.guide" link id2arexx.guide/main} for all commands description.

	There are only few most important commands available.

	The best way is to use Image Descriptor together with
	another program like Image Studio, ImageFX or even
	some web browser like Voyager or IBrowse.
	
	Imagine, you`ve want to convert all your ILBM images
	into PNG images but you want to keep all author and
	copyright notices. 

	Here comes Image Descriptor.

	Just make your own arexx script which loads each image
	into Image Descriptor, gets description, convert image
	with e.g. ImageStudio and then load it again into
	Image Descriptor and sets previously readed description.

	Or, a script which load image you`ve just downloaded from
	WWW and write it with special file comment so you know
	what image it is.

	Image Descriptor ARexx interface doesnt provide any string,
	file or screen requesters. Only simple info requester can be
	opened and a file requester (in this case the program thinks
	that this was mouse click on one of the button rather than
	arexx command).

	Maybe in next version will be more commands to flush, store,
	restore the image buffer to freeing some memory.
	For now it is only one command which does this.

	So, enjoy with making your own arexx scripts.

@ENDNODE
@NODE #art "Express yourself !"
	@{B}Express Yourself !
	------------------@{UB}

	Do you think that Image Descriptor logo is ugly ?

	Do you think that the author cant paint ??

	Do you think that you can paint better than author ???

	Do you want to be a part of Image Descriptor development ????

	Do you ... 


	Yes! Now you can. Just load your favourite paint program
	and make your own Image Descriptor logo !
	
	Since v2.3 it is possible to replace original logo with your
	own. This feature is only available for OS 3.x becouse
	of using datatypes. The image format is not important 
	as long as you have required datatype installed.
	(OS 2.x users will get empty area)
	
	The image must be 80x190. Bigger images will be cut. Smaller
	will look ugly.

	The program will scan following locations for file "ID2GUI.PIC":

	"PROGDIR:" (drawer from Image Descriptor was invoked)
	"S:" drawer
	"ENV:ImageDescriptor" drawer

	in exactly the same order. In case of fail the default logo
	will be used.

	NOTE:
		if you are running on low memory machine than
		it is recommended to not use this feature
		becouse it require additional memory for that
		external logo. remember that or expect "out of mem" !

@ENDNODE
@NODE #1 "Introduction"
	@{B}Introduction
	------------@{UB}

	Today, in the Era of Internet where so many data is transferred from 
	one company to another, from one computer to another and finally from 
	one user to another, it looks like the data has belongs to no one.

	But that is not truth. All files belongs to someone who create them.

	Ofcourse not all of them are protected by the law or copyrighted. 
	Many of them are done for enjoment or educational purposes.

	In both cases a problem appears. How to sign our own work ? There are 
	as many utilities as possibilities.
	
	Almost each file format has its own place to store author name, 
	copyright notice or some misc comment.

	Also, almost each paint program or sound editor has possibility to add 
	these informations to files it save.

	There are three image formats that are very popular today becouse of 
	Internet. 

	· GIF 	which is available in two versions: still (87a) and animated (89a)
		in fact the last one can be also still. 
	· JPEG  excellent file format for photorealistic images (photos).
	· PNG 	which is alternative for GIF and sometimes may be alternative 
		for JPEG.

	There are many other image formats which are specific to some other 
	platforms, like BMP for W!ndows etc.

	Amiga has also its own image format, IFF-ILBM.
	Very old image format with rather low compresion level,	but very fast to 
	display.

	Currently most of the paint programs support all of above and allows to 
	sign them.

	However, there are situations when it is not comfortable to use such paint 
	program. Imagine that you have a small image and you want to sign it. 
	You have also a low-mem situation and there is not enough mamory to load 
	any of your favourite paint program. Or you just dont want to wait for 
	whole program to load just for this one image (not mention the time required
	for decompression).

	So what to do ?

	You can ofcoure use some small programs for this purpose or use 

				Image Descriptor


	Image Descriptor supports IFF-ILBM, GIF, JPEG and PNG images.

	Just paint all your images, scans them or whatever and save them into one 
	directory and with one step sign all of them. 

	Furthermore, Image Descriptor can comunicate with others via ARexx interface,
	so you dont need even to exits your paint program. 
	Everything will be done automagically !

	From now, all your images will be signed with your name	so everyone will know 
	who paint them and where to find him.

	Some features of the program:

	· MUI user interface
	· Possibility to describe whole directory
	· Options to rename multiple files at once
	· Options to modify file comments
	· View images directly from program or with external viewer
	· Preview option for some images
	· URL detection, OpenURL library support
	· 3 different string class to select for your enjoyment
	· very easy to use
	· it`s FREE

@ENDNODE
