@NODE #5 "Requirements"
	@{B}Requirements
	------------@{UB}

	Image Descriptor 2 is designed to work in
	Hires Interlaced (640x512) resolution
	or higher.

	But it should work with	lower resolutions.

	Screenmode with 256 colors or more is also
	good idea. 

	Image Descriptor 2 should not be launched
	from CLI if stack size is lower than 8192 bytes.

	Image Descriptor 2 requires:

	· Magic User Interface (MUI) v3.8
	· asl.library v38 or higher
	· AmigaOS 2.0 or higher (created on 3.0 but should work on 2.0)
	· some free memory
	· some images ...

	Recommended:

	· AmigaOS 3.0 or higher for internal viewer

	If Image Descriptor 2 is unable to locate any of
	above (except images) or there is not enough memory
	it will warn you about that.

	Used but not required:

	· more free memory (for big images)
	· hard disk
	· openurl.library (Web Browser and/or E-mail client)
	· BetterString.mcc
	· TextInput.mcc
	· Dtpic.mui
	· datatypes (ILBM, GIF, JPEG, PNG)
	· def icons for images
	· image viewers

@ENDNODE
@NODE #8 "Usage"
	@{B}Usage
	-----@{UB}
	
	Image Descriptor 2 can be launched from CLI or WB.
	The program doesnt take any arguments or tooltypes.

	The main window is divided into 4 pages.
	Also pulldown menu and context menu are available.

	Default page after start is File page.

	Pages:
   
	· @{" File   " link #page_file}
	· @{" Note   " link #page_note}
	· @{" Image  " link #page_info}
	· @{" About  " link #page_about}

	· @{" File Comment support " link #fcoment}
	· @{" URL detection " link #URL}

	· @{" Bubble help " link #bubble}
	
	· @{" Pulldown and context menu " link #menu}

	· @{" Prefs " link #prefs}

@ENDNODE
@NODE #menu "Pulldown and context menu"
	@{B}Pulldown and context menu
	-------------------------@{UB}

	The pulldown and context menu are designed to simplify work with
	program. All most important options are available here. You dont
	need to walk from one page to another anymore.

	Pulldown menu have also options to view help files and send e-mail
	to author.

@ENDNODE
@NODE #prefs "Prefs"
	@{B}Prefs
	-----@{UB}
	
	@{B}String class@{UB}

	- Standard
	- BetterString
	- Textinput

		MUI string class that should be used

	@{B}Viewer type@{UB}

	- Internal datatypes viewer

		With this you can select with viewer type you prefer.
		The internal viewer will use OS 3.0+ datatypes system.

	- User defined external viewer
	
		When you select external viewer additional options
		show up where you can select external viewer's path
		and arguments.
	
	@{B}Loading@{UB}

	- Ask before leaving MultiFile mode

		Normally, Image Descriptor warns you before leaving
		MultiFile mode. Here you can disable this warn
		requester.

	- Get file comment

		Disable / enable file comment reading.

	- Detect JPEG thumbnails

		This disable / enable thumbnail detection rutine.
		If you disable this the Preview option will not work.

	@{B}Saving@{UB}
	
	- Empty info removes existing description

		This feature, when disabled allows you to change specified
		description.(this option works only with ILBM and PNG images)

		Normally, the program removes all descriptions from image
		while saving and writes only these filled on Note page.
		But sometimes it is useful to only change ie. Author name
		without removing the rest of descriptions (which may be
		diffirent for each file).

		Just disable this option and the program will replace
		only these descriptions fields filled on Note page.

	- Remove JPEG embedded thumbnail

		When enabled, cause the program to remove JPEG embedded
		thumbnail.

	- Remove JPEG Extension Segment

		When enabled, cause the program to remove JPEG Extension
		Segment.

		This segment is designed to hold thumbnail.
	
		It is strongly recommended to NOT remove this becouse
		Image Descriptor use this thumbnail for its Previev
		option. 

		If you have fast computer you can enable this options
		and view the whole image but if you have rather slow
		machine	then thumbnails are the best solution for you.

	- Remove Exif marker

		When enabled, cause the program to remove JPEG Exif marker.
			
		An Exif marker appears in some JPEG images.
		Usually this marker replaces standard APP0 JFIF marker
		and makes that image unviewable with some viewers.

		This markers are created by some Digital Cameras.

		(if your software is unable to view such images
		removing Exif marker will not help. but if you
		can view it you may remove this marker and that
		image should be still viewable but the file will
		be a little smaller)

	- Remove Adobe markers

		When enabled, cause the program to remove (most) Adobe 
		markers	from JPEG image.

		These markers are not used by any Amiga software as
		far as i know and hold some information required
		by Adobe Photoshop.

		Sometimes Adobe marker can hold thumbnail, so if
		the Preview option is available and there is no
		info about thumbnail on Image page you can be
		sure for 100% that Image Descriptior found thumbnail
		in Adobe marker.
		
	@{B}MultiFile options@{UB}

	- Enable new MultiFile mode

		This new multifile mode is available since v2.3 but
		in v2.4 it is enhanced a little.

	- Disable fiole scanning

		When new MultiFile mode is enabled Image Descriptor
		will scan all selected files to check if they are
		images or not. This information is also used by
		Create HTML option.

		Unfortunatelly, scanning large directories can take
		some time and it is not always needed.

	- Take MultiFile type from first image

		When working in MultiFile mode you need to specify
		the image type that will be described.

		This is only way to inform Image Descriptor which
		images should be ignored and which to describe.

		By default ILBM is selected. 

		When you enable this option Image Descriptor will
		use first recognized image type as multifile image
		type.
	
	@{B}Icon options@{UB}

	- Save icons
		
		The program will add icons to saved image.
		
		You need def_ilbm.info, def_jpeg.info, def_gif.info
		and def_png.info in your ENV:sys drawer.

	- External viewer is icon Default Tool

		When this option is enabled the defined external viewer
		will be set as the icon Default Tool.

		So if you double click this icon from Workbench the same
		viewer will be called like in Image Descriptor.

	@{B}Misc@{UB}
	
	- Enable file requester filtering

		This options enables filtering in file requester.

		It is useful when you have a lot of files and you
		are not sure which of them are images.

		File requester will show you only supported files.

		This works very similar to WBPattern file requester
		which show only images that can be loaded by datatypes
		system.
		
	@{B}Last Save path@{UB}

		This is not really an option.

		It is used as storage for last save path only.


	There are also few options for Clean Up.
	
	- Remove File Comment
		
		Clears file comments

	- Remove icon

		Deletes icons associated to selected files.

	- Remove JPEG thumbnail, Extension Segment, Exif marker, Adobe markers
		
		Same as for global prefs.


@ENDNODE
@NODE #page_file "Pages / File page"
	@{B}File Page
	---------@{UB}

	This page is divided into 4 parts.

	First is file info. 

	When you load image you will see here its filename, size in bytes and image 
	type. However, if you select more than one image you will see a information 
	indicating that	program is now working in multi file mode together with
	number of selected files and a file type selector.

	Next is file comment.

	A file comment can be writed for saved image. This options allow you
	to choose which type of file comment you wish to write.
	It can be your own text, fiole comment based on image information or
	you can just clean file comment if already present.
	
	And finally there are four buttons.
	
	These buttons provide standard operations like open and save.
	The Save button will be disabled as long as you enter some text
	on Note page. You can also paste image from clipboard.
	The last button (Clean up) just saves image without any description.
	You can also drop icon into ID window to load image.	
	
	There is one more option only visible if program working in multi file
	mode. This option allows you to rename all selected files according
	to given pattern. Also an extension can be specified if you dont
	want to let the program do this.

@ENDNODE
@NODE #page_note "Pages / Note page"
	@{B}Note Page
	---------@{UB}

	Contents of this page depends of image type currently loaded into
	memory. There are different options for each image type.

	Following description types are available:

	for ILBM - Title, Author, Copyrights, Annotation
	for GIF - Comment
	for PNG - Title, Author, Copyrights, Comment, Software (read only)
	for JPEG - Comment

	There is also a listview available for each image type.
	If an Internet adress is present in image description it will be
	placed here. Double click on it and Web Browser defined in
	OpenURL library prefs will be called.

	Additionaly, if the jpeg image is loaded and it hold Digimarc
	information (NOT watermark) a special button will pop up.

	If you click it A Web Browser will be called and pointed to
	image's author/owner Web Site.

@ENDNODE
@NODE #page_info "Pages / Image page"
	@{B}Image Page
	----------@{UB}

	This page is replacement for Info and View page from previous versions
	of Image Descriptor.

	From now image information and view button are placed together on
	the same page. There is only one view button available for both
	datatypes and external viewer. Just select with Prefs which should
	be used.

	This page is also available in MultiFile mode starting from this
	version but it looks a little different than in SingleFile mode.

	There is no image information here, instead of this there is a listview
	with all selected files. 

	There is also a popup menu with following options:

	- View image
		
		This will show you the selected image

	- Show Info

		This will show you image information together with
		thumbnail (if available)

	- Take note

		You can take description from selected image instead of
		typing it by hand.

		Useful when you have some image collections and you wish
		to add some new images but you also wish to have the same
		description.
		
	Additionaly, with the "Make HTML" option you can create html list
	of all images that are actually selected in MultiFile mode.

	the list looks like this:

		Directory description created by Image Descriptor 2.3
			Copyright (c) 2000 @{U}Tomasz Malerczyk@{UU}

	Filename						Type	Size
	-----------------------------------------------------------------------
	@{U}foobar.jpg@{UU}						JPEG	3252
	@{U}photo.gif@{UU}						GIF	41000
	-----------------------------------------------------------------------
									2 images.

	All underlined texts are hyperlinks, so if you click i.e. foobar.jpg your
	Browser will be pointed to this image and it should show it to you.

	Also my name is underlined, click it and you can send me an e-mail.
	(ofcourse you need e-mail client and your Browser must be properly
	configured)

	
	Note, that v2.4 allows to disable file scanning. This affect also
	the HTML creation and only filenames will be used. 
	(without type and size info)

@ENDNODE
@NODE #page_about "Pages / About page"
	@{B}About Page
	----------@{UB}

	If you would like to know who made this program and how to contact him
	this page is good place for this.

	There are also version number, Internet adress and e-mail adress.

	At the bottom of this page you can also check name of ARexx port.

@ENDNODE
